						               													<description>Scruble Cube (Swedish and Finnish: Alfapet Twist) consists of a 4x4x4 Rubik's Cube, except a letter (along with the letter's point value) appears on each exposed side of each sub-cube. These letters are attached on circular pegs that freely rotate. This enables you to rotate each letter so that you can spell words in any direction.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players have 90 seconds manipulate the cube to form a word in a straight line that may wrap around the cube. Other sub-cube faces have Scrabble-type point modifiers such as double letter score or tripe word score. You get to use these point modifiers if they appear at the beginning or end of your word. A variant allows you to use these modifiers to represent any letter. Players also score bonuses if their word covers more than one face and if it intersects a previously created word (and that word still appears on the cube).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the web site of the game, http://www.scrublecube.com/:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you can spell you can play ... SCRUBLE Cube!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What if you took some of the known playing patterns of some of the most popular word games and puzzles in history and combined them in a brand new, unique format to create the World&amp;rsquo;s Greatest 3-D Word Game?  Well, you&amp;rsquo;d have the SCRUBLE Cube, a patent pending game with over 7.4 x 10^45 (that&amp;rsquo;s 7,401 septillion)  possible configurations that anyone who can spell can play. And all in a portable format that can be played anywhere -- anytime. The SCRUBLE Cube is a word game and a puzzle -- on steroids!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
